race.comment: TOKYO STAR (9) hasn't won for 87 weeks but this looks a nice race for her. Went back then came very wide on the bend and worked home well for fourth last start over this course and distance. A strong tempo will suit her racing pattern and Tommy Berry taking over adds to the confidence. DORADUS (2) led for home in the same race as TOKYO STAR here last time out and tried hard but found the winner too strong late. Not likely to get much peace up front this time but he is racing too well to rule out. EMBALLEE (7) has been thereabouts since a win three months ago. Worked home steadily to grab third at her latest appearance over 1550m here. Untried beyond the mile but her racing style suggests it will suit. MAREBELLO (6) led from the outset to register a tough maiden win recently over 1600m at Kembla. Progressive four-year-old who is from a Zabeel mare so the longer trip may see further improvement. DEALT (8) is ready to find some form at the fourth run back from a spell.
